# Draft Technical Document Template

Apply this rule when producing markdown technical documents.

## Core requirements

- Include an Abstract section in every document.
- Start Abstract with a bold context subheading and one to two context sentences.
- State the core deliverable in the Abstract.
- Include compact key-output tables in the Abstract.
- Avoid table-of-contents summary tables.

## Structure and style

- Put structured data in tables instead of prose.
- Add a bold title line directly above each table.
- Use bold subheadings to break multi-concept sections.
- Keep rationale concise, one sentence per idea when possible.
- Avoid repeating the same information across sections.
- Layer content for decision makers first, engineers second.

## Defaults and precedence

- Default to terse writing when no verbosity is specified.
- Default audience is decision makers and engineers.
- Follow explicit user formatting instructions when they conflict with this rule.
- Exclude workspace-specific output-routing constraints unless explicitly requested.
